# Conventional Commits

Follow [Conventional Commits v1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- Use imperative mood in the description: `add prompt` not `added prompt`.
- Keep the subject line ≤ 72 characters.
- Scope is optional but encouraged for this project (e.g. `shell`, `parser`, `builtin`).

## Types

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New stage behavior or user-facing capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests only |
| `refactor` | Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature |
| `chore` | Tooling, config, or maintenance |

## Examples

```
feat(shell): print $ prompt on startup

feat(parser): tokenize quoted arguments

fix(builtin): handle exit with no status code

test(parser): add table-driven tests for quote escaping
```

## Breaking changes

If a change is breaking, append `!` after type/scope and add a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.
